[[File:Star_Wars_Roleplaying_Game_Saga_Edition_Core_Rulebook.jpg|thumb|right|251px|The ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Saga Edition Core Rulebook]]'']]
'''''Star Wars Saga Edition''''' is the final [[roleplaying game]] system released by [[Wizards of the Coast]] in 2007 with its production lasting until 2010. Its ''[[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Saga Edition Core Rulebook]]'' features a new game system from the previous system, the [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game Revised Core Rulebook|''Revised Core Rulebook'']]. It was called ''"Saga Edition"'' because it was the first game to span the complete Star Wars film saga, encompassing all six feature films from [[Star Wars: Episode I The Phantom Menace|Episode I ''The Phantom Menace'']] to [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']]. Wizards of the Coast's entire [[Star Wars Roleplaying Game|Star Wars roleplaying]] production line ran from 2000 until 2010. After that, the license was granted to [[Fantasy Flight Games]] in 2011, who began work on a new roleplaying system called ''[[Star Wars: Edge of the Empire]]''.

As in all of Wizards of the Coast's Star Wars roleplaying games, Saga Edition's game rules are based on the [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/D20_System d20 System] similar to the third edition of [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dungeons_%26_Dragons Dungeons and Dragons].

Wizards of the Coast produced a total of 14 books for the Saga Edition. Also released during the Saga Edition production era was ''[[Dawn of Defiance]]'', a campaign comprising ten downloadable adventures designed as one story arc that takes characters from level 1 to the maximum level 20. Also released were a great many web supplements, including [[Jedi Counseling]] articles, of which articles #100-115 dealt with Saga Edition, and a Saga Edition Conversion Guide, which showed how to convert characters from the previous Revised Core Rulebook to Saga Edition.

The ''Core Rulebook'' won a number of [http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ENnie ENnie awards], including Gold in the "Best Game" category and the "Best Rules" category, as well as Silver for "Product of the Year" in 2008. ''[[The Clone Wars Campaign Guide]]'' won a Silver in "Best Supplement" in 2009.

